FORMAT: 1A
HOST: http://localhost:5000

# Library Management API

A simple API for managing books in a library.

# Group Books

## Books Collection [/books]

### Get all books [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
          {
            "id": 1,
            "title": "Clean Code",
            "author": "Robert C. Martin",
            "published_year": 2008
          }
        ]

### Create a new book [POST]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "title": "Domain-Driven Design",
          "author": "Eric Evans",
          "published_year": 2003
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
          "id": 2,
          "title": "Domain-Driven Design",
          "author": "Eric Evans",
          "published_year": 2003
        }

## Book [/books/{bookId}]

+ Parameters
    + bookId: 1 (number, required)

### Get a book by ID [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "id": 1,
          "title": "Clean Code",
          "author": "Robert C. Martin",
          "published_year": 2008
        }

+ Response 404

### Update a book [PUT]

+ Request (application/json)

        {
          "title": "Clean Architecture",
          "author": "Robert C. Martin",
          "published_year": 2017
        }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
          "id": 1,
          "title": "Clean Architecture",
          "author": "Robert C. Martin",
          "published_year": 2017
        }

### Delete a book [DELETE]

+ Response 200
+ Response 404